        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "GCI < 5% on hemolysis index QoI",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index computed per Celik et al. (2008) on three meshes (3.1 M, 8.7 M, 24.2 M cells). GCI on normalised hemolysis index must be less than 5% at the worst-case operating point."
      },
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation and GCI analysis performed on three systematically refined meshes at 5 L/min, 3500 RPM (identified worst-case point). Fine-grid GCI of 2.1% on the normalised hemolysis index confirms discretization error is well within the 5% acceptance threshold. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
