        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Experimental test conditions match COU operating envelope",
        "description": "Blood analogue fluid properties (viscosity, density), pump rotational speed, and flow rates in the validation experiment must fall within ±5% of the CFD boundary conditions used for the COU assessment."
      },
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experiments used a glycerol-water blood analogue (viscosity 3.5 cP, density 1050 kg/m³) matching CFD fluid properties within 2%. Five operating points (3–6 L/min, 2500–4000 RPM) span the COU envelope. Test conditions criterion satisfied at level 2."
    },
    {
