        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Normalised hemolysis index within validation uncertainty band",
        "description": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) must agree with experimental measurements within the combined experimental and numerical uncertainty band (U95) at all 5 operating points."
      },
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH values at all 5 operating points fall within the U95 combined uncertainty band (experimental U95 = ±0.18 mg/100L; numerical U95 = ±0.09 mg/100L). Maximum model-experiment discrepancy of 11% is within the validation acceptance band. Output comparison criterion satisfied."
