        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI directly maps to clinical hemolysis decision criterion",
        "description": "The primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly traceable to the clinical acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device) and must be computable from CFD outputs without unvalidated post-processing transformations."
      },
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is computed directly from the power-law hemolysis model integrated over CFD shear stress and exposure time fields. RH < 1 maps directly to the regulatory acceptance criterion for predicate device comparison. No unvalidated transformation steps are interposed. QoI relevance criterion satisfied."
