      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Formal model form uncertainty quantification is scoped out at MRL 2. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al. correlation) is the accepted industry standard for CFD hemolysis prediction and has been validated against the FDA benchmark dataset. Turbulence model sensitivity was assessed informally (k-ω SST vs. realizable k-ε; <8% difference in NIH). Full model form UQ not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/model-inputs-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Formal model input uncertainty propagation is scoped out at MRL 2. All geometric inputs are derived from FDA-published CAD files with documented tolerances. Fluid property inputs are traceable to calibrated laboratory measurements. A qualitative sensitivity screening identified rotational speed and fluid viscosity as dominant inputs; their nominal values are well-characterised. Full probabilistic UQ not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3."
    },
